Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I think it's better for freshman to live on camp during the first year of college. College life is a different life journey as any before it. Freshman need time to get used to it. So, live on campus will save a lot effort than living in a rental house. And living in a dorm can also be convinient go to other buildings on campus, such as library.